The 1 million masks, goggles, gloves, gowns and other protective gear for health workers, as well as ventilators for patients, will be flown on later in the day to 5 African countries; Djibouti, Sudan, Eritrea, Somalia and Tanzania. “From those five hubs they will be dispatched in as many countries as possible,” WFP Spokesperson, Elisabeth Byrs told a United Nations (UN) briefing in Geneva. The supplies are enough to protect health workers while treating more than 30 000 patients across the continent, she added. --Reuters-- 